---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Nav from '../components/Nav.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import '../styles/global.css';
---
<Layout title="Cookie Policy — Prestique" description="How Prestique uses cookies on its website.">
  <Nav />
  <main class="pt-32 pb-24 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto prose-blog">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-white mb-2">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-p-muted text-sm mb-12">Last updated: March 29, 2026</p>

      <p>This policy explains how Prestique LLC uses cookies and similar tracking technologies on prestique.ai and audit.prestique.ai.</p>

      <h2>What Are Cookies</h2>
      <p>Cookies are small text files placed on your device when you visit a website. They allow the site to remember information about your visit — such as your preferences or session state — to make the experience work correctly and improve over time.</p>

      <h2>Cookies We Use</h2>

      <h3>Essential Cookies</h3>
      <p>These cookies are required for the website to function. They cannot be disabled. They include cookies that maintain your session when using the audit tool and ensure the site loads correctly.</p>

      <h3>Analytics Cookies</h3>
      <p>We may use analytics cookies (such as Google Analytics) to understand how visitors use our site — which pages are visited, how long people stay, and where they come from. This data is aggregated and anonymous. You can opt out via your browser settings or Google's opt-out tools.</p>

      <h3>Advertising Cookies</h3>
      <p>When we run paid advertising campaigns (including Google Ads and Meta/Facebook Ads), those platforms place cookies on your device to measure ad performance and, where you've consented, to show you relevant ads. These cookies are set by third parties and governed by their respective privacy policies:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Privacy Policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/privacy/policy/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Meta Privacy Policy</a></li>
      </ul>
      <p>We will update this section when advertising campaigns go live and specific pixels or tags are added to the site.</p>

      <h2>How to Control Cookies</h2>
      <p>You can control and delete cookies through your browser settings. Most browsers allow you to block all cookies or block third-party cookies specifically. Note that blocking essential cookies may affect site functionality.</p>
      <p>Additional opt-out tools:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Analytics:</strong> <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a></li>
        <li><strong>Google Ads:</strong> Manage at <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">adssettings.google.com</a></li>
        <li><strong>Meta Ads:</strong> Manage at <a href="https://www.facebook.com/adpreferences" target="_blank" rel="noopener">facebook.com/adpreferences</a></li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
      <p>We will update this policy when new cookies are added to the site — particularly when advertising campaigns launch. Check this page for the current list.</p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>Prestique LLC<br />North Carolina, United States<br /><a href="mailto:support@prestique.ai">support@prestique.ai</a></p>
    </div>
  </main>
  <Footer />
</Layout>
